<div id="review_3664057593" class="review" itemprop="reviews" itemscope itemtype="http://schema.org/Review">
  <link itemprop="url" href="https://www.goodreads.com/review/show/3664057593" />
    <a title="Desca Ang" class="left imgcol" href="/user/show/25616429-desca-ang"><img alt="Desca Ang" src="https://images.gr-assets.com/users/1611538119p2/25616429.jpg" /></a>

  <div class="left bodycol">
    <div class="reviewHeader uitext stacked">
        <a class="reviewDate createdAt right" href="/review/show/3664057593?book_show_action=true">Nov 26, 2020</a>

      <span itemprop="author" itemscope itemtype="http://schema.org/Person">
        <a title="Desca Ang" class="user" itemprop="url" name="Desca Ang" href="/user/show/25616429-desca-ang">Desca Ang</a>
      </span>

        rated it
        <span class=" staticStars notranslate" title="really liked it"><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p10">really liked it</span><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p10"></span><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p10"></span><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p10"></span><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p0"></span></span>

          <span class="greyText">&nbsp;&middot;&nbsp;</span>
          <a class="lightGreyText" title="Hardcover 9780600609001" href="/book/show/234196.The_Perfumed_Garden">review of another edition</a>


        

          <div class="uitext greyText bookshelves">
            Shelves:
              <a class="actionLinkLite" href="/review/list/25616429-desca-ang?shelf=umar-ibn-muhammed-al-nefzawi">umar-ibn-muhammed-al-nefzawi</a>, 
              <a class="actionLinkLite" href="/review/list/25616429-desca-ang?shelf=tunisian-writer">tunisian-writer</a>, 
              <a class="actionLinkLite" href="/review/list/25616429-desca-ang?shelf=a-scott-duane">a-scott-duane</a>
          </div>
    </div>


        <div class="reviewText stacked">
              <span id="reviewTextContainer3664057593" class="readable"
              >
            
<span id="freeTextContainer4582933786545259661">The review is taken from my Instagram account: <a href='https://www.instagram.com/p/CGwN7J_Ag2z/' rel='nofollow noopener'>@descanto</a><br/><br/>The Perfumed Garden is a fifteenth-century Arabic erotic literature written by Muhammad ibn Muhammad al-Nefzawi, also known simply as &quot;Sheikh Nefzawi&quot;.<br/><br/>In this book, the sheikh firstly praises God for giving the pleasure in love-making. He says thay God has granted women with the beauty, a man weaknesses but it also inspires them to make love to them. The Sheikh also states that he is a Muslim and Laa ilaaha illallah - there is only one God </span>
  <span id="freeText4582933786545259661" style="display:none">The review is taken from my Instagram account: <a href="https://www.instagram.com/p/CGwN7J_Ag2z/" rel="nofollow noopener">@descanto</a><br /><br />The Perfumed Garden is a fifteenth-century Arabic erotic literature written by Muhammad ibn Muhammad al-Nefzawi, also known simply as "Sheikh Nefzawi".<br /><br />In this book, the sheikh firstly praises God for giving the pleasure in love-making. He says thay God has granted women with the beauty, a man weaknesses but it also inspires them to make love to them. The Sheikh also states that he is a Muslim and Laa ilaaha illallah - there is only one God and that Mohammed is his prophet; he himself is only the servant of God. The rest of the book is similar to Vatsyāyāna's Kamasutra, they present the author's opinions in the pleasure department. It includes the materials that men and women should have to attract each other, the sexual techniques, recipe and warnings about sexual health and maladies.<br /><br />Penis and vagina are listed with different names completed with the interpretation of dreams and how to reach the self-fulfilment in the pleasure department.<br /><br />My copy of book is translated by the famous Sir Richard Burton from French. I've always loved his translation esp on 1001 Arabian Nights. Have you ever read his translation work? The book is also completed with beautiful erotic illustrations. I was surprise to have found this book at Kota Gede for a reasonable price knowing that this book is a piece of classic erotica. My only disappointment is that they removed the chapters about homosexuality in this edition. I do not know the reason why but it is probably because of the sake of its circulation.<br /><br />A good book tho...with greater erotic illustrations.<br /></span>
  <a data-text-id="4582933786545259661" href="#" onclick="swapContent($(this));; return false;">...more</a>

          </span>
