<div id="review_2603564088" class="review" itemprop="reviews" itemscope itemtype="http://schema.org/Review">
  <link itemprop="url" href="https://www.goodreads.com/review/show/2603564088" />
    <a title="Mitch Flitcroft" class="left imgcol" href="/user/show/47456512-mitch-flitcroft"><img alt="Mitch Flitcroft" src="https://images.gr-assets.com/users/1557219276p2/47456512.jpg" /></a>

  <div class="left bodycol">
    <div class="reviewHeader uitext stacked">
        <a class="reviewDate createdAt right" href="/review/show/2603564088?book_show_action=true">Nov 23, 2018</a>

      <span itemprop="author" itemscope itemtype="http://schema.org/Person">
        <a title="Mitch Flitcroft" class="user" itemprop="url" name="Mitch Flitcroft" href="/user/show/47456512-mitch-flitcroft">Mitch Flitcroft</a>
      </span>

        rated it
        <span class=" staticStars notranslate" title="liked it"><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p10">liked it</span><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p10"></span><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p10"></span><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p0"></span><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p0"></span></span>



        

    </div>


        <div class="reviewText stacked">
              <span id="reviewTextContainer2603564088" class="readable"
              >
            
<span id="freeTextContainer9103132253893592145">I stumbled across this short book while reading about Richard Francis Burton. It’s a gem and a really interesting insight into the surprisingly erotic world of 15th-century Islamic sexuality. <br/><br/>Some parts are sexual: <br/><br/><blockquote>Thus it will be well to play with her before you introduce your verge and accomplish the cohabitation. You will excite her by kissing her cheeks, sucking her lips and nibbling at her breasts. Lavish kisses on her navel and thighs, and titillate the lower parts. Bite her arms, and negl</blockquote></span>
  <span id="freeText9103132253893592145" style="display:none">I stumbled across this short book while reading about Richard Francis Burton. It’s a gem and a really interesting insight into the surprisingly erotic world of 15th-century Islamic sexuality. <br /><br />Some parts are sexual: <br /><br /><blockquote>Thus it will be well to play with her before you introduce your verge and accomplish the cohabitation. You will excite her by kissing her cheeks, sucking her lips and nibbling at her breasts. Lavish kisses on her navel and thighs, and titillate the lower parts. Bite her arms, and neglect no part of her body; cling close to her chest, and show your love and submission.</blockquote><br /><br />Other parts are sexist: <br /><br /><blockquote>Contemptible likewise is the woman who is constantly laughing out; for, as it was said by an author, 'If you see a woman who is always laughing, fond of gaming and jesting, always ruling to her neighbours, meddling with matters that are no concern of hers, plaguing her husband with constant complaints, leaguing herself with other women against him, playing the grand lady, accepting gifts from everybody, know that that woman is a whore without shame.</blockquote><br /><br />Like many old pieces of literature, it is well-written and a pleasure to read. Most surprising to me was the acceptance of lust and emphasis on foreplay and enjoyment of sex, which were parts largely neglected in the Christian tradition. However, the book becomes a little boring towards the end as it departs from sexuality and enters the realm of pseudoscience. Nevertheless, it’s an interesting little book. </span>
  <a data-text-id="9103132253893592145" href="#" onclick="swapContent($(this));; return false;">...more</a>

          </span>
        </div>


